frameDefinitions: An Entity is obscure, unnotable, and in general little-known.
Through use, a Resource is diminished in quality or quantity (up to complete attrition) such that it becomes less capable of sustaining future use.
An Entity is presented as having been seen or experienced by a (typically generic and backgrounded)
An Entity began its existence in the context of a location of Origin, which is a discourse-salient place, or culture.
An Entity is well-known among a wide range of people (in general or in a particular domain) for a particular Reason, which may be a behavior, characteristic, or some other associated item.
A Cognizer has a piece of Content in their model of the world.
frameExamples: Geoffrey Rush was <t>little</t> <t>known</t> outside his native Australia when he soared to international prominence.
My entire life savings is <t>depleted</t> due to university and medical bills.
Susanna Fulton's work is <t>new</t> to me.
Obviously there are species that are <t>native</t> to China or used in Chinese Medicine that aren't used in Western or Cherokee Medicine and vice versa.
Shakespeare was <t>famous</t> during his life because he performed in front of Queen Elizabeth I more than anyone else.
Your boss is <t>aware</t> of your commitment.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Entity</fen> which is not widely known and rather obscure.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is not well known.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is not famous.
The <fen>Resource</fen> is a physical entity or an ability to perform work that was used in an earlier process, typically in pursuit of a goal.
A concrete thing or abstract phenomenon or fact that is assessed in terms of how well recognizable it is to a <fen>Cognizer</fen>.
The (typically non-specific and backgrounded) sentient being for whom the <fen>Entity</fen> possesses a specified level of recognizability.
The deviation of the actual level of recognizability of the <fen>Entity</fen> from the level specified by the target.
The item whose <fen>Origin</fen> is under discussion.
The discourse-salient place or culture where the <fen>Entity</fen> was produced.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which is widely known and recognized.
The behavior, attribute, or associated entities that provide the reason for the <fen>Entity</fen> being famous.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.

The <fen>Cognizer</fen> is the person whose awareness of phenomena is at question. With a target verb or adjective the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is generally expressed as an External Argument with the <fen>Content</fen> expressed as an Object or Complement.
The <fen>Content</fen> is the object of the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s awareness. <fen>Content</fen> can be expressed as a direct object or in a PP Complement.
Some verbs in this frame allow a <fen>Topic</fen> to be expressed in about-PPs.
<fen>Expressor</fen> is the body part that reveals the <fen>Cognizer</fen>'s state to the observer.
The time interval during which the <fen>Cognizer</fen> is aware of the <fen>Content</fen>.
listRoleExamples: Certain academic works are obscure <fex>only in North America</fex>.
He gave <fex>an address</fex> quite familiar to the chauffeur.
The information used to illustrate the concept is familiar <fex>to the reader</fex>.
He gave an address <fex>quite</fex> familiar to the chauffeur.
This station is famous <fex>for the many ramen shacks surrounding it</fex>.
Certain people are well known <fex>only in North America</fex>.
<fex>Your boss</fex> is aware of your commitment.
Your boss is aware <fex>of your commitment</fex>.

Yet there is no evidence that Mr. Parrish was cognizant <fex>at the time of the signing
of the notes</fex> that the clauses in issue were present.
